reviews.review: Suffers from following TLJ because it has to introduce a big bad, start from nothing, get Rey trained & end a saga. It does it, but only just. We had a trilogy of story packed into two movies in reality with TLJ still having a negative impact on the SW universe.
Standard Star Wars story, everything is in line and like it should be. Payed critics should be avoided just go to theater and watch movie, it is worth it.
Once again, ignore the critics. Movie is amazing. Go see it.

JJ did a good job in trying to pull in all the lose threads from the past two movies. I went into the cinema thinking the movie was going to be terrible, I was happy to be proven wrong. It's to bad we won't get to see The last Jedi through the eyes of JJ it would of been a great set up to this last film and for characters and general lore but that isn't the case so rots has some people feeling it was a little rushed and out of left field, but ultimately still feeling like a Star Wars movie.

It was outstanding way to conclude the Skywalker Saga!! It tied all 3 trilogies together with great nostalgia and class.  While also leaving the door open for the franchise to continue if they choose with our 3 heros from the new Trilogy.  Ignore the critics and go see it.  A must for even a casual Star Wars fan!
We loved it! A mix of old and new. Great throw back lines. Great closure to the stories.

It was not perfect but it was fast paced , fun and captured the imagination. Easily the best of the sequels. I left the theatre feeling happy and wishing it was longer.  
Sure I wished some scenes were longer and some characters had more to do but it never took away from the overall plot .

There are allot of silly thing in it but its better then the last jedi for sure. In overall a really bad planned trilogy with a few good moments and a whole lot off missed opportunities. It such a same that blockbuster movies are so full of plot holes and cheese moments.This was the only mainstream franchise that i could still find a bit interest in but i think with Disney  i'll stick with the more quality movies.
Just horrible to see my childhood die again like the terminator, such a disrespect to the franchise, lore and the fans. I mean Rey ...Rey Skywalker are you fucking kidding me.
